node.text:
Maybe it’s the fact that it was 46 degrees when I woke up this morning (🍁!), or maybe it’s the overall feel of homeyness and place, but I find myself being really drawn to warm, inviting spaces these days.

The beautiful warm texture and color of these cabinets are speaking to me today - plus you know I love that #blackwhiteandwood look 🖤 It all adds up to one beautiful, cozy and inviting vibe.
Design by @blancmarineliving
Photography by @sylvieli 
.

node.text:
I showed you this hallway #beforeandafter from my #LHIStGeorge reno a month ago, but I love this view so much that I’m sharing it again 😆 3 things I especially love about this shot: 1) It shows how pretty those green kitchen cabinets are juxtaposed by the red in the brick flooring. I always end up with a few  views from every home that I especially love, and this may be one of those from this home 🥰 2) It gives you a peek of the vintage art we found for this home. We scoured local thrift and antique shops for vintage art, and I LOVE the charm the vintage paintings add to this home 3) We updated so many things about this home built in 2004, but I love the nod to the original architecture that little half arch gives 👍
What’s your favorite thing about this freshened up view?
.
Hallway lighting by @oldebricklighting 
.
.
.
.

node.text:
A dark and rainy day calls for a moody powder bath shot. Powder baths are the perfect place to bring in some drama and create an impact 🖤 We used BM French Beret in the bathroom and I love how it changes with the natural lighting. On bright sunny days, it has a navy blue vibe, and on dark rainy days like today, it’s feel like a rich black 🖤 Also@still in love with that pretty @lilicementtiles floor 🙌
.
